Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOdette%20categorises%20the%20usage%20of%20water%20into%20a%20framework%20she%20calls%20%E2%80%98Ecowaternomics%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20water%20needs%20hierarchy%2C%20similar%20to%20Maslow%E2%80%99s%20hierarchy%20of%20needs%2C%20based%20on%20a%20hierarchical%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20defines%20the%20concept%20as%20being%20economical%20with%20water%20usage%2C%20using%20only%20the%20bare%20minimum%20that%20one%20needs%2C%20and%20not%20as%20much%20as%20is%20abundantly%20available.%20This%20can%20be%20achieved%20by%20two%20principles%3A%20use%20less%20and%20reuse%20more.%20Using%20less%20is%20obvious%20but%20needs%20reminding%20(low%20tap%20flow%2C%20tap%20off%20when%20not%20needed%2C%20no%20running%20water%2C%20and%20no%20leaks).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20next%20question%2C%20%E2%80%9CWould%20you%20bathe%20with%20mineral%20water%3F%E2%80%9D%20emphasises%20the%20second%20part%20of%20her%20formula%20%E2%80%93%20to%20reuse%20more.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20waste%20water%20of%20higher%20purity%20to%20bathe%2C%20yet%20we%20all%20use%20fresh%20water%20out%20of%20a%20tap%20for%20washing%20mops%20or%20rinsing%20dirty%20dishes%20when%20water%20of%20lower%20purity%20works%20just%20as%20easily%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20her%20calculations%2C%20she%20says%20most%20households%20require%20fresh%20water%20for%20only%2030-40%20percent%20of%20their%20needs%2C%20remaining%20water%20needs%20can%20be%20met%20by%20reusing%20this%20water.%20%E2%80%9CWater%20that%20you%20let%20down%20the%20drain%20is%20always%20good%20for%20some%20other%20purpose%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20suggests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20points%20out%20the%20hidden%20sources%20of%20water%20available%20at%20the%20household%20level%3A%20water%20from%20washing%20hands%2C%20rice%2Fpulses%2C%20fruits%20and%20vegetables%2C%20waste%20RO%20water%2C%20water%20from%20defrosting%2C%20and%20washing%20machine%20outlet%20water.%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20these%20are%20not%20fit%20for%